{"title_page": "Nicky Evrard", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Nicky Evrard\n| image              = Nicky Evrard 2014 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size         =\n| caption            = \n| fullname           = Nicky Evrard\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1995|05|26}}\n| birth_place        = [[Zottegem]], [[Belgium]]\n| height             = {{height|m=1.74}}\n| position           = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub        = [[Sporting de Huelva|Sporting Huelva]]\n| clubnumber         = \n| youthclubs1        = Racing Strijpen\n| youthyears1        = \n| youthclubs2        = SK Munkzwalm\n| youthyears2        = \n| collegeyears1      =  | college1 = |collegecaps1 =  |collegegoals1 = \n| years1 = 2013\u20132017 | clubs1 = [[AA Gent (women)|AA Gent]] | caps1 = 50  | goals1 = 0 \n| years2 = 2017\u20132019 | clubs2 = [[FC Twente (women)|FC Twente]] | caps2 = 42 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2019\u2013 | clubs3 = [[Sporting de Huelva|Sporting Huelva]] | caps3 = 0 | goals3 = 0\n| nationalteam1      = Belgium U15\n| nationalyears1     = 2009\u20132010\n| nationalcaps1      = 2\n| nationalgoals1     = 0\n| nationalteam2      = Belgium U17\n| nationalyears2     = 2010\u20132012\n| nationalcaps2      = 15\n| nationalgoals2     = 0\n| nationalteam3      = Belgium U19\n| nationalyears3     = 2012\u20132013\n| nationalcaps3      = 6\n| nationalgoals3     = 0\n| nationalteam4      = Belgium U21\n| nationalyears4      = 2014\n| nationalcaps4      = 1\n| nationalgoals4     = 0\n| nationalteam5      = [[Belgium women's national football team|Belgium]]\n| nationalyears5     = 2013\u2013\n| nationalcaps5      = 30\n| nationalgoals5     = 0\n| club-update        = \n| nationalteam-update = 1 June 2019\n}}\n\n'''Nicky Evrard''' (born 26 May 1995) is a Belgian [[Association football|soccer]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] who plays for Spanish [[Primera Divisi\u00f3n (women)|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] club [[Sporting de Huelva]] and the [[Belgium women's national football team|Belgium women's national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.belgianfootball.be/en/national-womens-team-selection|title=National Women's Team selection \u2013 Royal Belgian Football Association|website=www.belgianfootball.be}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nEvrard started her career at Racing Strijpen and SK Munkzwalm boys teams. In the 2011/2012 season, she signed with Cercle Melle. In 2012, the team change its name to [[AA Gent (women)|AA Gent]]. In the 2016/17 season, she won the Cup of Belgium with AA Gent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nicky Evrard (KAA Gent 2011\u20132017)|url=https://www.facebook.com/notes/vzw-voetbal-in-de-stad/nicky-evrard-kaa-gent-2011-2017/1917570871601708/|website=Facebook|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref> On 17 May 2017, Evrard announced that she would be joining [[FC Twente (women)|FC Twente]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Van Der Meulen|first1=Eline|title=Red Flame Nicky Evrard ruilt Gent voor Twente|url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/9090/Voetbal/article/detail/3161190/2017/05/18/Red-Flame-Nicky-Evrard-ruilt-Gent-voor-Twente.dhtml|website=HLN|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Nicky Evrard (KAA Gent Ladies) kiest voor Nederlands avontuur! (met video)|url=http://nieuws.vrouwenvoetbal.be/?p=19513|website=Nieuws|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nFrom 2009 to April 2013, Evrard was part of several Belgium's youth teams. On 2 June 2013, she played for Belgium senior team for the first time in a friendly match against [[Ukraine women's national football team|Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Belgi\u00eb 3 \u2013 0 Oekra\u00efne|url=http://www.belgianfootball.be/nl/wedstrijd_verslag/dames-belgi%C3%AB-oekra%C3%AFne-3-0|website=Belgian Football|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref> Evrard was also part of the team who represented Belgium at the [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017]].<ref>{{cite web|title=23 Belgian Red Flames in EK-selectie|url=http://www.belgianfootball.be/nl/nieuws/23-belgian-red-flames-ek-selectie|website=Belgian Football|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.uefa.com/teamsandplayers/players/player=250023764/profile/index.html Player's Profile at UEFA]\n* {{Soccerway}}\n* [http://static.belgianfootball.be/project/publiek/jrinteren/speler_PF_373.htm#itop Player's Profile at Royal Belgian Football Association]\n\n{{Belgium squad UEFA Women's Euro 2017}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Evrard, Nicky}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women's association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Belgian women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from East Flanders]]\n[[Category:People from Zottegem]]\n[[Category:Belgium women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:BeNe League players]]\n[[Category:Super League Vrouwenvoetbal players]]\n[[Category:AA Gent (women) players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie (women) players]]\n[[Category:FC Twente (women) players]]\n[[Category:Belgian expatriate <!-- women's -->footballers]]\n[[Category:Belgian expatriate sportspeople in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Belgian expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate women's footballers in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Expatriate women's footballers in Spain]]\n\n{{Belgium-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Nicky Evrard\n| image              = Nicky Evrard 2014 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size         =\n| caption            = \n| fullname           = Nicky Evrard\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1995|05|26}}\n| birth_place        = [[Zottegem]], [[Belgium]]\n| height             = {{height|m=1.74}}\n| position           = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub        = [[Sporting de Huelva|Sporting Huelva]]\n| clubnumber         = \n| youthclubs1        = Racing Strijpen\n| youthyears1        = \n| youthclubs2        = SK Munkzwalm\n| youthyears2        = \n| collegeyears1      =  | college1 = |collegecaps1 =  |collegegoals1 = \n| years1 = 2013\u20132017 | clubs1 = [[AA Gent (women)|AA Gent]] | caps1 = 50  | goals1 = 0 \n| years2 = 2017\u20132019 | clubs2 = [[FC Twente (women)|FC Twente]] | caps2 = 42 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2019\u2013 | clubs3 = [[Sporting de Huelva|Sporting Huelva]] | caps3 = 0 | goals3 = 0\n| nationalteam1      = Belgium U15\n| nationalyears1     = 2009\u20132010\n| nationalcaps1      = 2\n| nationalgoals1     = 0\n| nationalteam2      = Belgium U17\n| nationalyears2     = 2010\u20132012\n| nationalcaps2      = 15\n| nationalgoals2     = 0\n| nationalteam3      = Belgium U19\n| nationalyears3     = 2012\u20132013\n| nationalcaps3      = 6\n| nationalgoals3     = 0\n| nationalteam4      = Belgium U21\n| nationalyears4      = 2014\n| nationalcaps4      = 1\n| nationalgoals4     = 0\n| nationalteam5      = [[Belgium women's national football team|Belgium]]\n| nationalyears5     = 2013\u2013\n| nationalcaps5      = 30\n| nationalgoals5     = 0\n| club-update        = \n| nationalteam-update = 1 June 2019\n}}\n\n'''Nicky Evrard''' (born 26 May 1995) is a Belgian [[Association football|soccer]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] who plays for Spanish [[Primera Divisi\u00f3n (women)|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] club [[Sporting de Huelva]] and the [[Belgium women's national football team|Belgium women's national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.belgianfootball.be/en/national-womens-team-selection|title=National Women's Team selection \u2013 Royal Belgian Football Association|website=www.belgianfootball.be}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nEvrard started her career at Racing Strijpen and SK Munkzwalm boys teams. In the 2011/2012 season, she signed with Cercle Melle. In 2012, the team change its name to [[AA Gent (women)|AA Gent]]. In the 2016/17 season, she won the Cup of Belgium with AA Gent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nicky Evrard (KAA Gent 2011\u20132017)|url=https://www.facebook.com/notes/vzw-voetbal-in-de-stad/nicky-evrard-kaa-gent-2011-2017/1917570871601708/|website=Facebook|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref> On 17 May 2017, Evrard announced that she would be joining [[FC Twente (women)|FC Twente]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Van Der Meulen|first1=Eline|title=Red Flame Nicky Evrard ruilt Gent voor Twente|url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/9090/Voetbal/article/detail/3161190/2017/05/18/Red-Flame-Nicky-Evrard-ruilt-Gent-voor-Twente.dhtml|website=HLN|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Nicky Evrard (KAA Gent Ladies) kiest voor Nederlands avontuur! (met video)|url=http://nieuws.vrouwenvoetbal.be/?p=19513|website=Nieuws|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nFrom 2009 to April 2013, Evrard was part of several Belgium's youth teams. On 2 June 2013, she played for Belgium senior team for the first time in a friendly match against [[Ukraine women's national football team|Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Belgi\u00eb 3 \u2013 0 Oekra\u00efne|url=http://www.belgianfootball.be/nl/wedstrijd_verslag/dames-belgi%C3%AB-oekra%C3%AFne-3-0|website=Belgian Football|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref> Evrard was also part of the team who represented Belgium at the [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017]].<ref>{{cite web|title=23 Belgian Red Flames in EK-selectie|url=http://www.belgianfootball.be/nl/nieuws/23-belgian-red-flames-ek-selectie|website=Belgian Football|accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.uefa.com/teamsandplayers/players/player=250023764/profile/index.html Player's Profile at UEFA]\n* [http://uk.scoresway.com/www.bcmegabasket.net?sport=soccer&page=player&id=175715 Player's Profile at Scoresway]\n* [http://static.belgianfootball.be/project/publiek/jrinteren/speler_PF_373.htm#itop Player's Profile at Royal Belgian Football Association]\n\n{{Belgium squad UEFA Women's Euro 2017}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Evrard, Nicky}}\n